-- Brazil's Caixa to raise up to $1 bln in global bond issue
-- By Aluisio Pereira
-- Tue May 06, 2014 11:26AM EDT
-- None



SAO PAULO, May 6 (Reuters) - Brazilian state-run lender Caixa Economica Federal <CEF.UL> plans to raise up to $1 billion in a new global bond issue as early as Tuesday, a source with direct knowledge of the situation told Reuters.   (Reporting by Aluisio Pereira; Writing by Asher Levine)  ((asher.levine@thomsonreuters.com)(+55-11-5644-7756)(Reuters Messaging: asher.levine1.thomsonreuters.com@reuters.net))  Keywords: BRAZIL CAIXA EC FEDERAL/BONDS

